      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>orzo </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>to the pan with the <strong>chopped olives</strong> and 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
